An Act relative to motor vehicle battery storage.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Chapter 140 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after section 59A the
2 following section:-
3 Section 59B. All holders of a Class 1, Class 2 or Class 3 license pursuant to section 58,
4 all owners or operators of a motor vehicle repair shop registered pursuant to chapter 100A, all
5 owners or operators of a junkyard or automobile graveyard as those terms are defined in section
6 1 of chapter 140B or any person or entity who sells or stores motor vehicle batteries shall
7 prominently display notice to the public and first responders of the presence of motor vehicle
8 batteries on the premises. Violation of this section shall be subject to a civil penalty of $250.
